                  <summary>End of a letter evidently from a higher official to a lower, urging him to send some object. The order is accompanied by threat in cae of carelessness on the part of the official addressed.</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Some strips of papyrus have been glued on the verso and must be removed as separate fragments. They belong to the same papyrus (because of the forms of the preserved letters). They are not ancient or modern repairs (NL)</note>
                     <note type="general">Location: Ann Arbor</note>
                     <note type="general">Pub. status: Recto; Verso is unpublished (only a few traces of letters)</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
               </msContents>
